# Debugging Discipline

- When something isn't working, verify our own code's interaction patterns first — call ordering, caching, timing — before assuming upstream libraries have bugs.
- If the data is correct in the database but wrong at runtime, the problem is almost certainly caching or call sequencing, not a bug in the framework reading the data.
- Reading upstream source code is a last resort, not a first instinct. Most "bugs" are our code calling APIs in the wrong order or missing a side effect.

