# Code Review

> **Before any review, read `~/.claude/memory/code-review.md` first. For PR workflows, also read `~/.claude/memory/pr-workflow.md`.**

- When reviewing PRs for local repos, prefer checking out the branch with `git` rather than making repeated `gh api` / blob reads — the repo is already on disk
- Write review comments in a human voice — positive, constructive, and solution-oriented
- Always suffix PR review comments with `[ai authored; matt approved]`
{{- end }}

# Git Rebase

- When rebasing a PR branch, always start from a clean fork of the remote: `git reset --hard origin/<branch>` before rebasing. Never rebase from local branch state — it may be stale or diverged, leading to unnecessary force pushes.
- Fetch the remote branch and base branch before starting: `git fetch origin <base> <head>`

{{- if eq .role "work" }}

# Git Worktrees

- Use worktrees for PR reviews and any work that shouldn't disturb the current branch
- Worktree base path: `~/Code/.worktrees/<repo-name>/<branch-name>`
- Always clean up worktrees after the review/task is complete

